To Run
	Exicute: ./IonWake_EXE {Input Directory} {Output Directory} {Run Name}

Input Files
	params.txt
		Contains general input parameters for the simulation. Such as the timestep length
		and the radius of the dust particles.
	dust-params.txt
		Contains the initial positions and charges for the dust particles. 
	timestep.txt
		Is used to turn on and off several time step options.

Timestep Options
	TR-ion-pos
		Prints a trace of an ion's position to the trace output file.
	TR-ion-vel
		Prints a trace of an ion's velocity to the trace output file.
	TR-ion-acc
		Prints a trace of an ion's acceleration to the trace output file.
	CH-charge-dust
		Allows the dust charge to be dynamicaly calculated.
	CH-move-dust
		Allows the dust potision, velocity, and acceleration to be 
		dynamicaly calculated.
 
Sample parameter values from params.txt
	NUM_ION   		   60000
    DEN_FAR_PLASMA     1e14
